South Africa has recorded 1 745 new coronavirus cases. This brings the total number of cases to 676 084. The country has also recorded 132 new COVID-19 related fatalities, bringing the total number of deaths to 16 866. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in KwaZulu-Natal. “Regrettably, we report 132 more COVID-19 related deaths: “49 from KwaZulu-Natal, 41 from Mpumalanga, 8 from Gauteng, 7 from the North West, 7 from the Northern Cape, 6 from Western Cape and 14 from the Free State,” says Dr Mkhize. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 4 209 049. The number of recoveries now stands at 609 854, this translates to a recovery rate of 90%. 4 209 049 676 084 609 854 49 364 16 866 626 720 As at 01 October 2020 21 132 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 676 084, the total number of deaths is 16 866 and the total number of recoveries is 609 854. pic.twitter.com/Sw1XqAAQMF — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) October 1, 2020 